HEADWORD: Englishism
<hw>Eng"lish*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
quality or characteristic peculiar to the English.</def> <rj><au>M.
Arnold.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A form of expression peculiar to the English
language as spoken in England; an Anglicism.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Englishman</ent>⟦br⟧
